@node intro "Introduction"

 Oscilloscope plugin for AmigaAMP.
   
@endnode

@node install "Installation"
 
  This package contains four executables:

   for P96: BlurScopePIP        (window version)        
	    BlurScopePIPfs	(fullscreen version)	 	 	
   for CGX: BlurScopeOVERLAY	(window version)
	    BlurScopeOVERLAYfs	(fullscreen version)

  Copy the appropriate files into your PLUGINS dir 
  of AmigaAMP and use rescan from menu.

@endnode

@node require "Requirements"
                  
  
                  You will need some things:
                  --------------------------
    Hardware:
	-an AMIGA :-)
	-MC68020+
	-Graphics card with OVERLAY/PIP feature @{"Machines" link bugs }

    Software:
	-AmigaAMP
	-OS3.1+
	-Picasso96 V2.0 @{"Note for VooDoo3 users" link bugs}
	 or CGX3/4+cgxvideo.library

  
 
@endnode

@node use "Usage"
 
 Select the plugin from the PLUGINS menu.
 
 Window version:
  Your Workbench must be in 15/16/24/32 depth mode.
  
 Fullscreen version:
  A 800x600x16 screen will be opened.
  Quit with ESC.
        
@endnode

@node bugs "Known Bugs"


  Mediator+VooDoo3+P96: 
  ---------------------

  Window version: If your Workbench screen works in doublescan 
    mode,the OVERLAY data will not be displayed correctly in its window.
    This not the program's fault! This will be happened with all other 
    programs,which uses the PIP/OVERLAY mode.(e.g.Frogger,AMP2,etc.)
  
  Fullscreen version: VooDoo3 needs the P96 2.0a package!
  In 800x600 screenmode the DOUBLESCAN must be turned off.

  Bugs? Questions? @{"Author" link author }

  The plugin has been tested on the following configurations:

    A1200 BlizzardPPC/040+Mediator+VooDoo3 (P96)
    A1200 BlizzardPPC/040+BVision (CGX)


@endnode




